Geoapify Geocoding API is a REST-based service that converts human-readable addresses (e.g., building name, street, postal code) into geographic coordinates (latitude and longitude), and vice versa. It also supports reverse geocoding and retrieving nearby Points of Interest (PoIs), making it useful for location-based applications and map visualizations.

You can use it in your workflow to:

Convert extracted address data into coordinates
Enrich locations with nearby amenities (PoIs)
Enable spatial visualization in applications like Streamlit

https://www.geoapify.com/geocoding-api/
